<p class="article-lead">SDS, COA and IFRA documents answer different questions. Asking for “all certificates” can leave a buyer with many files but no evidence tied to the approved product.</p><dl><dt><strong>SDS</strong></dt><dd>Communicates hazard, handling, storage and transport-related information for a material or product. It is not a quality release certificate.</dd><dt><strong>COA</strong></dt><dd>Reports specified results or conformity for an identified batch or material, depending on the issuer's specification.</dd><dt><strong>IFRA Certificate of Conformity</strong></dt><dd>Is issued by the fragrance-mixture supplier for an intended use category; IFRA itself does not issue it.</dd></dl><p>Match every document to the exact product or fragrance reference, issuer, revision and intended use. None of these alone proves that the finished perfume may be sold in a destination market.</p>
